License

🧰 Getting Started
Fork the repository

Clone your fork

bash
Copy
Edit
git clone https://github.com/your-username/AiOps.git
cd AiOps
Create a branch for your feature or bugfix

bash
Copy
Edit
git checkout -b feature/your-feature-name
Install dependencies

bash
Copy
Edit
pip install -r requirements.txt
Run tests locally

bash
Copy
Edit
pytest tests/
🚀 Ways to Contribute
Submit bug reports 🐛

Suggest new features 🧠

Improve documentation 📚

Add or optimize ML models 🤖

Build new plugins (alerting, dashboards, integrations) 🛠️

Refactor or clean up code 🧼

🧪 Code Guidelines
Follow PEP8 standards

Use black for formatting

Run flake8 to check linting

Add unit tests for any new logic

Keep functions modular and well-documented

Follow the folder structure under /src and /tests

🔁 Pull Request Process
Push your changes

Open a pull request against the main branch

Ensure:

Tests are passing ✅

Code is linted and formatted 💅

The PR includes a clear description of what you changed and why

Before your pull request can be merged, you must sign the Contributor License Agreement (CLA) via CLA Assistant. See [CLA.md](./CLA.md) for details.

We will review and provide feedback within 2–3 working days.

🐞 Reporting Issues
If you find a bug or unexpected behavior:

Open an issue

Include:

Steps to reproduce

Expected vs. actual behavior

Screenshots or logs if possible

🌟 Community Standards
Be respectful and inclusive

Avoid spam or self-promotion

Keep discussions constructive

Follow the Code of Conduct (if applicable)

📄 License
This project is licensed under the MIT License.
By contributing, you agree that your code will be released under the same license.

🙌 Thank You!
We appreciate your interest in contributing to AIOps Enterprise. Together, we can build a smarter and more resilient operations ecosystem!

